snippet.title: Mercedes CLA 45 AMG S Emblem Swap DIY

In this tutorial, we show how to change the rear trunk emblem on a Mercedes CLA 45 AMG S from standard chrome to a sporty black finish ğŸ–¤. This small change gives the rear a much sharper and more aggressive look â€” perfect for a performance car like this.
Step by step process:
ğŸ“ First, apply painting tape under the emblem and mark dots with a pen â€” this creates a perfect template so you know exactly where to place the new badge.
ğŸ£ Use fishing line to cut through the glue between the emblem and the paint â€” safe and scratch-free.
ğŸ§¼ Remove the emblem, clean off the old glue with remover, polish the surface, and prepare it for the new badge.
âœ¨ Place the new black emblem in the exact same position using your template.
ğŸ”¥ The result is a clean, precise, and sporty accent that completely upgrades the rear look of the CLA 45 AMG S.
This method works on any car emblem â€” easy, safe, and fully reversible if you want to go back.
